org.apache.beam.it.jdbc

Class OracleResourceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.beam.it.testcontainers.TestContainerResourceManager<JdbcDatabaseContainer<?>>
      • org.apache.beam.it.jdbc.AbstractJDBCResourceManager<OracleContainer>
        • org.apache.beam.it.jdbc.OracleResourceManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.beam.it.common.ResourceManager, JDBCResourceManager

    public class OracleResourceManager
extends AbstractJDBCResourceManager<OracleContainer>
    Default class for the Oracle implementation of AbstractJDBCResourceManager abstract class.

    The class supports one database, and multiple tables per database object. A database is * created when the container first spins up, if one is not given.

    The class is thread-safe.
